Education Academy Set Up With Hong Kong Donation
CHANGCHUN September 21 ( Xinhua ) -- Construction of the Education Academy of Classical Learning was recently completed at the Northeast Normal University in northeast China 's Jilin Province .
Hong Kong businessman Tin Ka Ping donated eight million yuan ( about 970,000 U.S. dollars ) for the building of the academy , which was added to a state investment of ten million yuan .
With a total floor space of 11,000 square meters , the academy will provide a center for the university 's basic educational research , experimentation and teaching .
By the end of 1997 , Tin had donated to the building of 96 educational institutions in the Chinese inland areas .
His total donations to the country 's education now amounts to hundreds of millions of yuan .
